   Yeah, the $10 a month thing someone mentioned, I don't really think about that.  I think more in terms that people just have no respect for the fact that you might have better things to do.  Only take 5 minutes?  Don't I wish.  Maybe if I was only asked a couple times then yeah.  Try running around EC to get materials for leather padding (best zone for getting all materials you need for that) and stopping to buff every person who asks you.  Or you can try turning even one down politely, and listening to him shout to the zone how you're so incredibly greedy.<br>
<br>
   But anyway, that's not even the point I'm trying to make.  The point is that if something is worth the money to you, you pay it.  If you think something costs too much, then don't pay.  It's a free market economy.  Find someone who doesn't charge so much, or charges nothing at all.  Kantiz's actions were shameful, not because of any argument over whether a druid should charge for ports, but because her auction made it clear that money was expected, the amount being up to him, and he didn't pay her.  Simple as that.  And then made up a lame excuse about being in a hurry for a raid, which the raid leader already posted on this thread saying he was lying, because they were NOT waiting for him as he'd claimed.  The fact that he chose to make up a lie like that shows that he knew he'd done something a bit shady by running off without donating.<br>
<br>
And on top of all that, plain common fucking courtesy would suggest a bit of compensation for someone who was killed trying to port you for a fee, and had to pay for a rez.<br>
